# Development Workflow Guide

## Project Setup
1. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

2. Start development server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

## Key Commands
- `npm run dev`: Start development server with hot reload
- `npm run build`: Create production build
- `npm run preview`: Preview production build locally
- `npm run astro check`: Type-check your project

## Development Tools
- VS Code with Astro extension recommended
- Dev toolbar available in development mode
- TypeScript support enabled via [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)

## Project Configuration
- [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs): Main Astro configuration
- [remark-reading-time.mjs](mdc:remark-reading-time.mjs): Reading time plugin
- [content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts): Content collection schema

## Best Practices
1. Use TypeScript for type safety
2. Follow component structure guidelines
3. Keep content organized in collections
4. Use proper file extensions (.astro, .ts, etc.)
5. Maintain consistent code style
